+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Followed `AGENTS.md` in the workspace root. Classified all visible review
+threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing code.
+Only the required writable files were changed.
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+Authoritative triage output was written to `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Code and Doc Remediation
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  - Normalize `approval_state` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)`, so
+    fallback and live-preview payloads share the same normalized state.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  - Preserve `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the
+    `preview_unavailable` payload.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  - Expanded fallback assertions and added a regression test for
+    `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  - Updated the fallback JSON example and notes to reflect the corrected human
+    review fields.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `Ran 5 tests in 0.000s`
+- `OK`
+
+## Constraints Checked
+
+- No files under `.github/review_export/` were modified.
+- `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was not modified.
+- `tests/test_approval_router.py` was not modified.
+- No `legacy_preview_hint` field or equivalent legacy preview branch was added.
