+## Review Reply Draft
+
+### T-214-01
+
+Applied. The fallback branch in `src/policy/preview.py` now preserves both
+`approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled=False`, and
+`src/policy/approval_router.py` now normalizes `manual_review` before building
+either preview payload shape.
+
+### T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This was the same reopened fallback regression,
+so I handled it with the shared payload fix instead of a second code change.
+
+### T-214-03
+
+Not applied. The export marks this thread outdated, and the suggestion targets
+an obsolete hunk that would reintroduce legacy preview behavior on the current
+branch. No legacy preview hint or equivalent branch was added.
+
+### T-214-04
+
+Applied. `tests/test_preview.py` now includes a regression test that exercises
+`build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
+and asserts the fallback payload keeps
+`approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+### T-214-05
+
+Applied. `docs/approval_policy.md` now shows the corrected fallback payload,
+including `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
